<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Romatex three months shr weak, no div.</title>
<headline>Romatex three months shr weak, no div.</headline>
<dateline>CAPE TOWN 1997-02-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three months ended December 31, 1996 vs 12 months to September 30, 1996 and 12 months to September 30, 1995</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Headline Shr (cts)  0.1	vs   15.6	vs   92.1</p>
<p>    Div (cts)	     0.0	vs   4.0	 vs   43.5</p>
<p>    Attrib income	 0.1	vs   4.8	 vs   21.8</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		 0.1	vs   0.1	 vs   33.5</p>
<p>    Tax		     0.0	vs   4.7 loss  vs   11.7 gain</p>
<p>    Interest paid	 0.2	vs   1.5	 vs   1.8 gain</p>
<p>    Turnover		129.5    vs   505.3     vs   517.8</p>
<p>    Exceptional items   0.0	vs   0.0	 vs   1.0 loss</p>
<p>Full name: Romatex Ltd (clothing, footwear and textiles)</p>
<p>NOTE - A majority shareholding of the Romatex Group was acquired by Consolidated Frame Textiles Ltd from CG Smith Ltd last year. The group's financial year has thus been changed to June 30 bringing it in line with Confram.</p>
<p>Despite a difficult trading environment Romatex expects a modest improvement for the six months to June 1997.</p>
<p>-- Cape Town newsroom +27 21 252238</p>
